# Vivesca crontab (supercronic on soma)
# TZ = Asia/Hong_Kong (set via supervisor.conf, matches soma-watchdog/vivesca MCP)
# Format: m h dom mon dow  command
#
# All commands SHOULD go through soma-cron-wrap for env setup + logging.
# soma-cron-wrap sources .zshenv secrets, sets PATH, captures exit codes
# to ~/.local/share/vivesca/cron-runs.jsonl.
#
# Never migrate jobs that need macOS APIs (Chrome cookies, peekaboo, iPhone
# mirroring, osascript, etc.) — those stay on Mac. See:
#   ~/docs/solutions/soma-primary-migration-plan.md

# ── Pre-existing ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# evergreen: update Python + deps daily at 12:00 HKT
0 12 * * * soma-cron-wrap evergreen /home/vivesca/germline/effectors/evergreen /home/vivesca/germline

# ── Phase 2 migrations (added one at a time after end-to-end test) ──
# All added jobs were tested via `soma-cron-wrap <name> <cmd>` first.
# Mac equivalents still run in parallel until Phase 3 (DR gating) lands.

# Pilot: rotate-logs (Sunday 05:00 HKT) — low-stakes, idempotent
# Note: rotates SOMA's own logs (not Mac's) — Mac plist still rotates Mac logs.
# These are independent (different log dirs), no DR gate needed.
0 5 * * 0 soma-cron-wrap rotate-logs /usr/bin/python3 /home/vivesca/germline/effectors/rotate-logs.py

# pondus-monitor: daily model rankings check (read-only API call, idempotent)
# Mac plist also runs at 09:00 — duplicate API call until Phase 3 gating
0 9 * * * soma-cron-wrap pondus-monitor /home/vivesca/germline/.venv/bin/pondus monitor check

# wewe-rss-health: every 6h, checks WeChat RSS scraper health endpoint
0 */6 * * * soma-cron-wrap wewe-rss-health /home/vivesca/.local/bin/uv run --script --python 3.13 /home/vivesca/germline/effectors/wewe-rss-health.py

# update-coding-tools: every 2h on soma (apt + pip + uv + cargo updates)
# Mac runs hourly — soma runs less frequently (less code churn on server)
# These are independent (Mac updates Mac brew, soma updates soma apt) — no DR gate needed
0 */2 * * * soma-cron-wrap update-coding-tools /home/vivesca/germline/effectors/update-coding-tools.sh

# transfection: mirror ~/code/ git repos from soma to ganglion (every 15 min)
# Walks ~/code/*/.git, pipes owner/repo slugs to ganglion, clone-or-pulls each.
# Keeps ganglion ready as an mtor worker target for any repo Terry builds on soma.
*/15 * * * * soma-cron-wrap transfection /home/vivesca/germline/effectors/transfection

# cc-snapshot: save tmux pane → CC session ID mapping (every 2 min)
# Used by soma-cc-resume to restore sessions after restart.
*/2 * * * * python3 /home/vivesca/germline/effectors/soma-cc-snapshot
